HEADWORD: Rhinoscopy
<hw>Rhi*nos"co*py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Rhino-</ets> + <ets>-scopy</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The examination or study of the soft palate,
posterior nares, etc., by means of a laryngoscopic mirror introduced
into the pharynx.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rhinotheca</ent>⟦br⟧
